author_ssm: Lydia Brawner (2011); Finding aid completed by Rachel Greer (2012).
abstract_ssm: The Martha Wilson Papers consist of comprehensive documentation of the life and career of Martha Wilson, artist and Founding Director of Franklin Furnace, Inc. Materials include journals, correspondence, flyers and posters, articles, clippings, juvenilia dating from grade school onward, video recordings, and a computer disc. The collection also contains materials related to Wilson's son Comly Cook-Wilson, and restricted materials dealing with Wilson's finances and medical history.
